body:
#### Issue details
Using `batch.draw(...)` to draw a **TextureRegion** that was created with the default constructor, causes a NullPointerException. Since there is a default constructor `TextureRegion region = new TextureRegion()` I think this should not happen. If it should happen, the empty constructor should not be available.

#### Reproduction steps/code
Run this code:
```java
private TextureRegion region = new TextureRegion();
private SpriteBatch batch = new SpriteBatch();

private void draw()
{
  batch.begin();
  batch.draw(region, 0f, 0f, 1024f, 512f);
  batch.end();
}
```

This can be prevented by:

```java
private void draw()
{
  batch.begin();
  if(region.getTexture() != null) { batch.draw(region, 0f, 0f, 1024f, 512f); }
  batch.end();
}
```

#### Version of LibGDX and/or relevant dependencies
1.9.9

#### Stacktrace
```java
Exception in thread "LWJGL Application" java.lang.NullPointerException
	at com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.SpriteBatch.flush(SpriteBatch.java:960)
	at com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.SpriteBatch.end(SpriteBatch.java:185)
	at de.limbusdev.guardianmonsters.ui.AScreen.drawBackground(AScreen.kt:64)
	at de.limbusdev.guardianmonsters.ui.AScreen.render(AScreen.kt:80)
	at com.badlogic.gdx.Game.render(Game.java:46)
	at com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplication.mainLoop(LwjglApplication.java:225)
	at com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplication$1.run(LwjglApplication.java:126)
```

#### Please select the affected platforms
I guess all.
